sequenceDiagram
    actor C as Contractor
    participant UI as React Client
    participant SRV as Express Server
    participant ST as Stripe API

    rect rgb(235, 251, 238)
        Note over C, ST: 5a. Release Payment (job completed)
        C->>UI: Clicks "Release Payment"
        UI->>SRV: POST /payments/:jobId/capture
        Note right of SRV: ⚠ KYC Gate:<br/>Check kycVerified flag.<br/>If false → return 403<br/>with Stripe Identity URL
        SRV->>ST: stripe.paymentIntents.capture()
        ST-->>SRV: Funds captured ✓
        SRV-->>SRV: paymentStatus = "captured"<br/>job.status = "completed"
        SRV-->>UI: {ok: true, status: "captured"}
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 245)
        Note over C, ST: 5b. Refund (alternative — job cancelled)
        C->>UI: Clicks "Request Refund"
        UI->>SRV: POST /payments/:jobId/refund
        SRV->>ST: stripe.refunds.create()
        ST-->>SRV: Funds returned ✓
        SRV-->>SRV: paymentStatus = "refunded"<br/>job.status = "cancelled"
        SRV-->>UI: {ok: true, status: "refunded"}
    end

    rect rgb(248, 249, 250)
        Note over C, ST: 6. Post-Completion Reviews (optional)
        C->>UI: Submits review (1–5 stars)
        UI->>SRV: POST /reviews
        SRV-->>SRV: Review stored<br/>Average rating recalculated
        SRV-->>UI: 201 Created
    end
